OL,3,CNorth East Child Poverty Commission
OL,4,Crenews calls to scrap two-child
OL,5,Cbenefit cap
OL,7,FThe two-child cap policy was
OL,8,Fintroduced by the Conservative
OL,9,FGovernment in 2017. It has meant that
OL,10,Falmost all families having a third or
OL,11,Fsubsequent child ` both in and out of
OL,12,Fwork ` are no longer entitled to
OL,13,Freceive support for those children
OL,14,Fthrough Universal Credit or Child Tax
OL,15,FCredits.
OL,17,FThe North East Child Poverty
OL,18,FCommission (NECPC) said that this sees
OL,19,Fyounger children missing out on up to
OL,20,F#66 per week in support that their
OL,21,Folder siblings receive.
