OL,5,Cbenefit cap
OL,7,FThis is an increase on the 17,550
OL,8,Fhouseholds across the region the year
OL,9,Fbefore.
OL,11,FThe NECPC said the new data indicates
OL,12,Fthat around 62,000 babies, children
OL,13,Fand young people throughout the region
OL,14,Fare now living in families affected by
OL,15,Fthe policy.
